SIMPLE: throe
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Throe
<hw>Throe</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>⟦thorn⟧rowe</ets>, <ets>⟦thorn⟧rawe</ets>, AS.
<ets>⟦thorn⟧re⟦aacute⟧</ets> a threatening, oppression, suffering,
perhaps influenced by Icel. <ets>⟦thorn⟧r⟦amac⟧</ets> a throe, a pang, a
longing; cf. AS. <ets>⟦thorn⟧reowian</ets> to suffer.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Extreme pain; violent pang; anguish; agony; especially, one of the
pangs of travail in childbirth, or purturition.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Prodogious motion felt, and rueful <qex>throes</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A tool for splitting wood into shingles; a
frow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Throe</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Throe
<hw>Throe</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To struggle in extreme pain; to be
in agony; to agonize.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Throe</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Throe
<hw>Throe</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To put in agony.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thrombin</ent>⟦br⟧
